==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[infinitus]]''', from negative prefix '''[[in-]]''', ''not'', + '''[[finis]]''', ''end'', + perfect passive participle ending '''[[-itus]]'''

===Adjective===
'''infinite'''
# [[boundless]], [[endless]], without end or limits, uncountable, innumerable
# in mathematics, a number which is larger than any given number.
# (figurative) very large

